@tqchen @were  Hey I updated the code accordingly. By tweaking `TVMValueCast::Apply`, we could correctly dispatch `operator T()`, so `TVMPodValue_` could be automatically converted to the subclass of NDArray, like this [line](https://github.com/dmlc/tvm/pull/2613/files#diff-5ad555ad211a7b2248bd6a3734077572R22).

I haven't got a clear sense about the glue part.

Okay, we can probably design it as the following to keep consistent interfaces.

```cpp
class PassNode : RelayNode {
   std::string name;
   int opt_level;
   bool enabled;
   std::vector<std::string> required_passes;
   
   virtual SetPassContext();
   virtual Module operator(const Module& mod);
   virtual Module Run(const Module& mod);
   virtual Pass CreatePass(...);
   virtual void ResolveDependency();
};
```

`Pass` is a virtual class. There are actually only three major jobs, namely pass creation, pass execution, and dependency resolution. Then we can create different granularity of passes and implement `CreatePass()` and `ResolveDependency()`. Now each pass itself could be view as a pass manager and it globs required passes to resolve the dependency. 

The `Optimizer` could be actually replaced by a `SequentialPass` and it could be inherited from `Pass` as well. Its major role is to resolve dependencies among a sequence of passes and it also implements the `run` method but instead if runs a sequences of passes.

I think now we have a consistent interface, i.e. everything inherits from `Pass`, and it performs Module -> Module optimization. Users are also only required to interact with the `Pass` class.

Some design considerations:
1. Do we use setters or pass `PassContext`. I don't have strong preference.
2. Do we need `CreatePass` or just register it as we currently do? I think `CreatePass` is probably not needed because the creation of FunctionPass and SequentialPass should be different.
3. Do we need to have the meta info in the `Pass`? It seems that `SequentialPass` and `FunctionPass` should have different info though.
4. Should we open a new namespace for pass manager, say `_pass_manager`, or use the current `ir_pass` namespace?

@tqchen Anything else I missed for discussion? Let's have a final and elegant conclusion on the topics soon so that we can move forward.

Again, any comments and suggestions are welcome and appreciated:)
